{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"## Plan-refinement progress (2026-07-08, epic adept-hedge-stain continuation)\n\nRefined across 2 plan-review rounds. Round-1's 2 architectural blocks are RESOLVED in the description (no\nboundary translation → extend `_call_with_retry` to recognize retryable `HTTPError` 429/5xx, leaving acli_rest's\nraw raise UNCHANGED so the 8+ raw-HTTPError catchers are unaffected; write-safety via a per-retry dedup guard).\nRound-2 surfaced 6 more, all now with concrete resolutions (capturing so the continuation is claim-ready):\n\n### Resolutions for the round-2 blocks (code-verified)\n1. **\"Alert\" is concrete = a bridge alert via the existing `alert_store` channel** (the same path\n   `run_differs._emit_outbound_field_alerts` uses — deduped 24h window, fail-open), PLUS a nonzero manifest tally\n   field. Recovery failure emits BOTH. Spec this in What §3 + AC4.\n2. **Recovery miswiring CONFIRMED at `run_differs.py:351`**: `binding_store.recover_pending_bindings(applier)`\n   passes the `applier` MODULE, which has no `search_issues` → `AttributeError` into the fail-open swallow. Fix:\n   pass a real client (the AcliClient exposing `search_issues`). `recover_pending_bindings` (binding_store.py:438)\n   calls `client.search_issues(colon_label / hyphen_label)` — a real client makes recovery actually work.\n3. **Test coverage AC**: add `python -m pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/ -q` green ALONGSIDE\n   `tests/scripts/bridge/ -q` (both are in-scope test locations; every functional AC names its test file).\n4. **Retry-After fallback**: honor the `Retry-After` header on 429 when present; when ABSENT (Jira Cloud does not\n   guarantee it) fall back to the jittered exponential backoff (per ADR 0036). AC1 must test both.\n\n### Implementation seams (verified, for the implementer)\n- `_call_with_retry` (dispatch_one.py:100-144): add an `except urllib.error.HTTPError` branch — retry when\n  `status in (429, 5xx)` (Retry-After or jittered), re-raise otherwise; mirror the existing JiraAPIError branch.\n  Do NOT touch acli_rest.py's raw raise (acli_rest.py:61-63) — verified 8+ external catchers depend on it.\n- Per-retry dedup guard: wrap create/comment in a callable that re-runs the rebar-id JQL (create,\n  dispatch_one.py:196) / comment-marker (comment) check at the start of each attempt; short-circuit if present.\n- `bind_pending` before `create_issue` + persist; confirm after label attach (binding_store.py write-ahead doc:6-16).\n- Lease steal: `__main__.py:534-539` held-lock path → call `steal()` when the lease is EXPIRED (fence semantics\n  at `_ref_lock.py:470-533`); keep exit 3 for a live holder.\n\n### Status\nCODE-only, closeable (no live gates). Ready to finalize the plan (apply the 4 resolutions above → re-review →\nclaim → implement). Deferred this session in favor of closing A3 + C2 (both done + certified + green) and the\nwall-clock realities of the epic's live-gated tickets (B1, D1)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783565964542005001,"uuid":"c07bdfd8-565f-45bd-9566-a3110b0f3598"}